<paragraph id="A4858687A757667AB32027D5FDE82EAC" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A08B6DF69DDDBFFF9209F55959B59CE4" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<bibRefCitation id="A736BDF6967D70DCE5BBEB3AC4470261" author="Gerstaecker, A" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fuer Naturgeschichte" pageId="18" pageNumber="59" title="Mutillarum Americae meridionalis indigenarum synopsis systematica et synonymica." volume="40" year="1874">Gerstaecker (1874)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="DA53B6F8A5A8484AE159DBA6F31F92B3" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mutilla amabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">Mutilla amabilis</taxonomicName>
based on two female specimens, one from Alegrete, Rio Grande do Sul State, Brazil and another from 
<normalizedToken id="9FE32481C59800E3D2F5C0E2768F96AE" originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
, Entre 
<normalizedToken id="68B665EBFDDCB7F3C748C19F52BB3E26" originalValue="Ríos">Rios</normalizedToken>
Province, Argentina. The specimen from Alegrete, deposited in the ZMB and bearing the labels cited above, was examined and is herein designated as a lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADFF1E1F7BA261FC9660DFD362E79A74" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">
<bibRefCitation id="6045C6E5BACEFAAD07D74F57925F758A" author="Casal, OH" journalOrPublisher="Eos, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, Madrid" pageId="18" pageNumber="59" pagination="9 - 18" title="Darditilla nuevo genero neotropical de Sphaerothalminae [sic!] (Hym. Mutillidae)." volume="41" year="1965">
<pageBreakToken id="9148F548C20C86F31E02E2F5CFC4494E" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" start="start">Casal</pageBreakToken>
(1965)
</bibRefCitation>
hypothesized that 
<taxonomicName id="C11E9870537E28AD4C66F069202E32B3" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla botija" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="botija">Darditilla botija</taxonomicName>
was the male of 
<taxonomicName id="DFCF174B0943E2CD402537FCB68C73CC" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla amabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">Darditilla amabilis</taxonomicName>
based on geographical distribution in northern Argentina. Yet another overlapping distribution was found in Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul State, Brazil. Only two other 
<taxonomicName id="2E2ECCE7758FEF7CFEE4A1D9D0777524" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Darditilla</taxonomicName>
females are known from Rio Grande do Sul: 
<taxonomicName id="34D4B686A17417C098BA2E66DCBB2781" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla debilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">Darditilla debilis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="807A8CC94982046244109DDF177F569D" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla infantilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infantilis">Darditilla infantilis</taxonomicName>
(Burmeister, 1875). The male of 
<taxonomicName id="BF9A707A609B1D3B79417B849EA7F8FC" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla debilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">Darditilla debilis</taxonomicName>
is described below; 
<taxonomicName id="DC2151BF4A4F468B531E9EE2C80C5D4B" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla infantilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infantilis">Darditilla infantilis</taxonomicName>
is structurally similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DADBFE8D5D2A78265951227E02F73A3B" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla bejaranoi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bejaranoi">Darditilla bejaranoi</taxonomicName>
and has a consistently small body size, precluding it from association with 
<taxonomicName id="537F009105CC5A8B90762B7B46295328" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla botija" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="botija">Darditilla botija</taxonomicName>
. The newly described male of 
<taxonomicName id="6156B7C7D7E0B7E301535078D23DFB42" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla felina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felina">Darditilla felina</taxonomicName>
has similar genitalia and clypeal modifications to 
<taxonomicName id="B36F30D6A3E32FFE3E19FE9A3F5FC620" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla botija" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="botija">Darditilla botija</taxonomicName>
. Likewise, females of 
<taxonomicName id="A371760CE8BEDE3CACBF7BD70D54F4CC" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla felina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felina">Darditilla felina</taxonomicName>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="79F65A1C3834E06E9D7465672CD76E3F" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla amabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">Darditilla amabilis</taxonomicName>
in the integumental markings of T2 and the genal carina. Distribution, similar body size, and morphological similarities to both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="4781FB8B6528EDAF741AC97539485258" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla felina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felina">Darditilla felina</taxonomicName>
support the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="F9067FD192B06C246BE23AF859B4763B" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla botija" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="botija">Darditilla botija</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="8F03C52F7B02B4BFBBF37ECC002C5934" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla amabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">Darditilla amabilis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E350A37853573EE2429B0F6FE736101" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">
<bibRefCitation id="FEB3E45CC2F83BA414E13748E7E541E7" author="Burmeister, HCC" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Academia Nacional de Ciencias Exactas existente en la Universidad de Cordova" pageId="18" pageNumber="59" pagination="461 - 502" title="Mutillae Argentinae." volume="1" year="1875">Burmeister (1875)</bibRefCitation>
had briefly described the supposed male of 
<taxonomicName id="F018744BA7B3DAB6F075D9B52301C316" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mutilla amabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">Mutilla amabilis</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken id="1990815C59BA65324DBA73FA9F871801" originalValue="Paraná">Parana</normalizedToken>
, Entre 
<normalizedToken id="14D06A86140C0D9C78C2F6E225E131D9" originalValue="Ríos">Rios</normalizedToken>
, Argentina. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="DB8386A2950281968E82B1DD080FC7B4" author="Andre, E" journalOrPublisher="Anales del Museo Nacional de Buenos Aires (Ser. 3 a)" pageId="18" pageNumber="59" pagination="169 - 214" title="Etude sur les Mutillides du Musee National d'Histoire naturelle de Buenos Aires." volume="10" year="1908">
<normalizedToken id="3D63F8F9F12B79E28821A44DB04F51FB" originalValue="André">Andre</normalizedToken>
(1908)
</bibRefCitation>
studied and redescribed the male that 
<bibRefCitation id="DF834C4B1E2F6FF784F66552F1490C44" author="Burmeister, HCC" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Academia Nacional de Ciencias Exactas existente en la Universidad de Cordova" pageId="18" pageNumber="59" pagination="461 - 502" title="Mutillae Argentinae." volume="1" year="1875">Burmeister (1875)</bibRefCitation>
originally associated with 
<taxonomicName id="495101CAA5D72113C50A298CBCD2F067" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Mutilla amabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">Mutilla amabilis</taxonomicName>
; he pointed out that its identity and sexual association were doubtful. This male is clearly not conspecific with the male of 
<taxonomicName id="10CCD08EF9DD907EFD632B18186E08C5" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla amabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">Darditilla amabilis</taxonomicName>
described above, most notably differing in its reddish basal metasomal segments. The description of this putative 
<taxonomicName id="CB6A357BF9B5FB1BD6EEF9FDD0F68F13" authority="Casal, 1965" authorityName="Casal" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Darditilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Darditilla amabilis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">Darditilla amabilis</taxonomicName>
male is, however, consistent with some Argentinean 
<taxonomicName id="EF219129BE0E642321BEEC6CDCF982F9" authority="Ashmead, 1896" authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pseudomethoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudomethoca" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pseudomethoca</taxonomicName>
males.
</paragraph>
